FROM THE DESK OF Joseph Dubin
9-i4-76
Dear Jack--
I thought you should have the enclosed book. 
There's something funny going on in Moberly. I think us four big city slicks got the put-on. That FRONTIER LOUNGE--I'm pretty sure--is where we had supper and MET the cocktail waitresses. Yet the place across from the police station the guy pointed out to me--whom I'd met earlier at the FRONTIER-sure didn't look like it was in the same place.
Maybe I was in not too good shape to have my bearings straight--because 107 1/2 would be upstairs, yet I know the two young ladies said 107--and the Frontier has no downstairs. I guess it will always remain one of life's mysteries.
Stay well and as happy as we are these days. All well and happy here. Working hard and that makes a person feel good.
Salud,
Curt
Say hello to Gladys for me. Next time we'll all go out to the Frontier for dinner, no?
AM ENCLOSING YOUR FIRST XMAS CARD FOR THIS YEAR

Johnson, Curt
6232 N. Hoyne 1C
Chicago 60659
New Address
12-13-79
Dear Jack - 
Just a note to say hello. Haven't heard from you in a while so hope everything's okay there. 
Nothing going on here except I got three December Press books I have to get out pretty soon or the authors will put out a contract on me. Also I finished a novel not long back that Jay is having his agent try to piddle. And Jay is trying to start his Crime Newsletter. Put out 14,000 flyers 10 days ago and is now nervously awaiting what return subs there will be.
Weather holds good here - knock on wood. As I say, just a note. 
Best, 
Curt
